The paper deals with distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The algorithms are for finding maximal matchings and maximal independent sets, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The problem of finding maximal matchings and maximal independent sets also has connections to Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
